Title: Session Management Best Practices
Question: Which of the following is NOT a recommended practice for secure session management in Java web applications?
A. Regenerating session IDs after login
B. Setting appropriate session timeouts
C. Storing session IDs in localStorage for persistence
D. Implementing proper logout functionality

Correct Answer: C
Explanation: Storing session IDs in localStorage is not recommended because localStorage is accessible to JavaScript, making it vulnerable to XSS attacks. Session IDs should be stored in secure, HttpOnly cookies.
